        "title": "how to make wrapper works on mac os x",
        "body": "<p>I have a big projects working on a <strong>linux server<\/strong>, I downloaded the jars to my mac os x 10.10.1 machine.<\/p>\n\n<p>I changed the pom.xml to this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;generatorConfigurations&gt;\n    &lt;generatorConfiguration&gt;\n        &lt;generator&gt;jsw&lt;/generator&gt;\n    &lt;includes&gt;\n        &lt;include&gt;macosx-universal-64&lt;/include&gt;\n        &lt;include&gt;macosx-universal-32&lt;/include&gt;\n    &lt;/includes&gt;\n&lt;/generatorConfiguration&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When I run: two new files have been generated, which are:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>wrapper-macosx-universal-32\nwrapper-macosx-universal-64\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>However, I am getting these errors:\nUnable to locate any of the following operational binaries:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  /bla bla /bin/./wrapper-macosx-universal-64 (Found but not executable.)\n  /bla bla /bin/./wrapper-macosx-universal-32 (Found but not executable.)\n  /bla bla /bin/./wrapper\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I have no idea how to fix that.<\/p>\n\n<p>I found a jar called wrapper.jar, should I replace it with a jar for mac? if yes which one should I get from these <a href=\"http://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/doc/english/download.jsp\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://wrapper.tanukisoftware.com/doc/english/download.jsp<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>I am able to provide u with whatever information you need. <\/p>\n",
